data.text:
Welcome to Hoboken--Birthplace of Baseball and Frank Sinatra.

The first officially recorded, organized baseball match which was played on June 19, 1846 on Hoboken's Elysian Fields with the New York Base Ball Club defeating the Knickerbockers 23-1 in four innings. A plaque was erected by H.I.B.A. closer to Elysian Fields commemorating the event.

Frank Sinatra (Francis Albert Sinatra) was born, the son of Italian immigrants Natalie Della (née Garaventi) and Anthony Martin Sinatra, at 415 Monroe Street on December 12, 1915. The site is now an empty lot used for storage as the original tenement building burned down in the 1970s.
